text.section:
Property is not subject to State property tax if the property is:
owned by a land trust as defined in § 3-2A-01 of the Natural Resources Article that is certified by the Maryland Environmental Trust to be a land trust in good standing and to have a cooperative agreement in effect; and
used:
to assist in the preservation of a natural area;
for the environmental education of the public;
to conserve agricultural land and to promote continued agricultural use of the land;
generally to promote conservation; or
for the maintenance of a natural area for public use or a sanctuary for wildlife.
